**Evaluating file implementation issues**

It looks like our files have been overwritten by a different implementation, and it doesn't seem to have any blocked path or hashing mismatch validation. I think we need to make sure the current code addresses any potential path security issues—especially since the user requires blocked paths. The packet is blocked, but the current implementation doesn’t enforce these paths as our original did. I should consider merging in the blocked path and hash validation into the current implementation and inspect the rest of the artifact registry too.
